      "side": 1,
      "message": "I just noticed this CL, and wanted to comment...\n\nI don\u0027t think we need separate compression types for BC1 with and without alpha. I just looked at the MS BC1 docs, but they appear to be missing a really critical piece of information: The presence or absence of alpha is encoded on a per-block basis. If the endpoints are in ascending order, then the block should be decoded as (c0, (c0+c1)/2, c1, transparent), otherwise it should be lerps of c0 and c1 at 1/3 and 2/3.\n\nThe older DXT1 docs actually have these details: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/direct3d9/opaque-and-1-bit-alpha-textures",
